20180815_WorMotel_Heritability_subsampling

Tim C.

8/15/2018

This code uses processed survival data from Chris Fang-Yen’s lab to calculate heritability of survival traits. The data were collected in 2 blocks with 3 WorMotels per block (independent bleaches) by Matt Churgin at UPenn. Each block was prepared using HTA strain handling protocol from ECA lab. In all cases 11-12 strains were run on a single wormMotel with (20 nematodes / strain).

Traits

mean_int_b_activity = mean integrated base activity
mean_int_s_activity = mean integrated stimulated activity
mean_lifespan_days = mean lifespan days

2 blocks, 1 worMotel each

2 blocks, 2 worMotels each

2 blocks, 3 worMotels each


Sampled worMotels from blocks 3 and 4 only. The sampled worMotels had 3-20 worms per strain. I calculated H2 using block means of worMotel means.
